  "notes": "Standard Yoruba. 3-tone language: high (acute), low (grave), mid (unmarked or macron). P = /kp/ (labial-velar stop); GB = /ɡb/ (labial-velar). Ẹ = /ɛ/; Ọ = /ɔ/; Ṣ = /ʃ/. Nasal vowels marked with 'n' following vowel.",
